# Laravel Development

Aligned with `laravel-development` skill and global `laravel-superpowers`. **This project uses Repository + HasCache**, not a separate Service layer.

## Layer flow

```
Route → FormRequest → Controller → Repository (HasCache) → Model
                         ↓
                   API Resource
```

```php
// ✅ GOOD — thin controller
public function store(StoreNewsRequest $request): NewsResource
{
    $news = $this->repository->create($request->validated());
    return new NewsResource($news);
}

// ❌ BAD — logic in controller
public function store(Request $request) {
    $news = News::create($request->all());
    Cache::flush();
    return $news;
}
```

## Repository rules

- Extend `BaseRepository`; override `defaultSelect()`, `defaultWith()`, `searchableColumns()`.
- Reads: `$this->remember()` — writes: `$this->clearCache()`.
- Complex multi-model writes: `DB::transaction()` inside repository method.

## Model rules

- `$fillable` explicit; use `HasCommonScopes` (`active`, `published`, `ordered`).
- Casts in `casts()` method; no business logic beyond scopes/accessors.

## API

- **Form Request** per store/update — never inline `$request->validate()`.
- **API Resource** for all JSON responses — hide internal fields.
- Eager load in repository, not in controller.

## Jobs & events

Use when action has side effects (email, notifications) — dispatch from repository after successful commit:

```php
DB::transaction(function () use ($data) {
    $model = $this->model()::create($data);
    Event::dispatch(new NewsPublished($model));
    return $model;
});
```

## Performance (from laravel-superpowers)

- `select()` only needed columns; `with()` all relations used in Resource.
- `chunk()` / `cursor()` for exports — never `all()` on large tables.
- `paginate(15)` max 50 for list endpoints.
